<br>
I may not have a place in this discussion as:<br>
1 I did not go on this hate raid<br>
2 The Dragonchow are not members of the SGA (Hopefully this will change with time)<br>
<br>
But I do have some opinions (obviously) and I do read the SGA board dailey (at least for the last 2 weeks)<br>
<br>
Now, I have a pretty unique perspective on planes gear being a monk, we monks call our Shiverback armor Shivercrap, and most woud only wear the boots other than occasional resist here and there.<br>
<br>
With this in mind here are some of my suggestions/comments/opinions.<br>
<br>
First and foremost, considering that SGA is heading away from the &quot;Open&quot; raids to more controled SGA only raids, there should be at least some rules, senority, and or subjectivity.<br>
Second, all cash loot should be divided by the raid leaders to reimburse the people that spent money. Dont matter what cash loot, blue diamonds, or opals, or ruby crowns, it should go to those that bought the hate stones, peridots, and so on.<br>
Third, those that are attending after the break in, should be bringing their own stone, I had considered checking if me and some of my guild were welcome later in the day on sunday, but if I had, I would have been sure we had our own hate stone.<br>
Fourth on NoDrop gear, I do believe the Raid Leader and certian people, as determined by the raid leader get some loot as default, period. That Zenknight walked away from this entire raid with nothing but a bluediamond is quite sad IMHO.<br>
<br>
Now for my expanding.<br>
<br>
Certain raids have different goals.<br>
Some examples: (Once again I am not trying to tell anyone how to do things, I just consider myself somewhat unbiased do to the lack of need in most instances&quot;<br>
<br>
Zenknights Icewell keep raids:<br>
Of course these should be run and looted as he sees fit, but I believe the raid leader should have the right to divy out loot the way they would like, part of being raid leader. The stated goal of these raids has been better equipment for the SGA as a whole, so looking at the larger picture would be perfect.<br>
<br>
Planes Raids:<br>
Once again, run as the Raid leader wants to, cash loot should go to reimburse those that spend money, clerics, enchanters, hate stone buyers for hete, and so on.<br>
I will also comment on the fear raid where the ToE druid got a piece of planes gear. I would have to say that while a member of the Chow had to give up his droppable item, and this raid was more or less &quot;Open&quot; in nature, I do not feel someone from a guild that can run their own Planes raids should be at an open raid. Now I am not saying anyone did something wrong (except rolling-looting nodrop gear-during combat and without the raid leader saying to) I am just saying the raid was &quot;loose&quot; in nature, so there was little communications.<br>
Now on a raid the RL (raid leader) can be much too busy to divy out loot and settle disputes, there should be a &quot;Loot Boss&quot; designated by the raid leader.<br>
<br>
Thats about all I have for now, and as I have stated in the past, no loot rules are &quot;fair and perfect&quot; and all of this is just my personal take and opinions on the situation.<br>
Thanks for listening <p><TABLE>
